This is the original Prohunter NOT THE SPEED BREECH.  This model is so much better because it includes a tool that reaches inside the action turns and grabs the breech plug and pulls it out very easy.  My beech has never been stuck and is always easy to remove.  The speed breech model is toolless and you use you fingers..... that is until you shoot it a few times and then a gorillas fingers aren't strong enough to turn it.  Then you have to use pliers or locking pliers to turn the breech plug any mar up the outside of the breech.  I bought it new with a .50 caliber muzzleloader barrel factory installed from TC.  This is the model that you can interchange barrels to many different calibers.  I have never changed the barrels it is as factory as the day i got it.  There is bore is perfect is is shiny as new. I never left powder sitting in the barrel after hunting i would remove it every time.  The only thing that i can pick out is 3 small little dings right next to each other on the action itself.
